1
00:00:00,416 --> 00:00:07,833
This was my place, the guard opens the door
and says to me, go ahead, sir

2
00:00:08,000 --> 00:00:13,625
Sarcastically, meaning mocking words,
and I would go out to him

3
00:00:14,000 --> 00:00:22,000
At the door, he steps in one step,
ties my hands behind my back, blindfolds me, then takes me

4
00:00:22,916 --> 00:00:27,250
Of course he would always take me,
and he would do this move the most

5
00:00:27,791 --> 00:00:32,166
There was a lot of humiliation in it,
he grabs you from behind like this, or pushes your head down hard

6
00:00:34,375 --> 00:00:42,250
That is what I remember,
moments like these are impossible to forget

7
00:00:42,625 --> 00:00:45,375
Interviewer: How long did you stay in this place?

8
00:00:45,583 --> 00:00:47,791
In this place,
I stayed exactly 12 days

9
00:00:48,291 --> 00:00:50,833
Interviewer: How did you spend
your time in this place?

10
00:00:50,875 --> 00:00:55,625
In this place, if we imagine
this door, we enter here

11
00:00:55,875 --> 00:01:03,833
Here was the food they left for you, which consisted of
jam, halva, olives, they left it here for you

12
00:01:03,875 --> 00:01:08,458
You always had this,
there were exactly two shelves here

13
00:01:09,208 --> 00:01:13,833
There was a Quran, Sahih al-Bukhari,
and Tafsir Ibn Kathir

14
00:01:14,791 --> 00:01:22,375
There was a nail clipper here, the room was carpeted
with a decent carpet, not bad

15
00:01:22,500 --> 00:01:26,500
The blankets were clean,
a person should speak the truth, the cleanliness was excellent

16
00:01:27,250 --> 00:01:32,333
Here, this was built with cinder blocks,
a concrete wall

17
00:01:32,375 --> 00:01:35,041
But it was not part of the original construction,
clearly it was new construction

18
00:01:36,250 --> 00:01:39,625
This here, pardon me,
was the bathroom and toilet

19
00:01:41,083 --> 00:01:44,500
When we go in here,
they would place the cleaning supplies here

20
00:01:45,708 --> 00:01:50,333
Laundry detergent,
if someone wanted to wash their clothes

21
00:01:51,333 --> 00:01:54,250
Shampoo for fungus and lice,
and things like that

22
00:01:54,458 --> 00:01:59,875
Regular shampoo, laurel soap,
and dish soap

23
00:02:00,375 --> 00:02:06,000
Dish soap, in case someone wanted
to wash the dishes after meals and give them back

24
00:02:06,875 --> 00:02:12,125
There were two water taps here,
I remember a hot water tap and a cold water tap

25
00:02:12,625 --> 00:02:15,458
And hot water was available,
because the weather was a bit cold

26
00:02:17,833 --> 00:02:25,791
Here there was an exhaust fan,
and there was an old sponge or loofah here

27
00:02:28,666 --> 00:02:35,000
Here was a sponge, two pillows,
this wall of course

28
00:02:35,958 --> 00:02:41,458
Usually here, the tiles were all exposed,
meaning the place was carpeted here

29
00:02:41,916 --> 00:02:46,000
Up to approximately here,
and the tiles here were all exposed

30
00:02:46,666 --> 00:02:51,875
One of the ways I would pass the time
was counting the tiles

31
00:02:52,500 --> 00:02:59,583
I never mixed with other prisoners,
I saw nobody until the last day when we came out

32
00:03:00,291 --> 00:03:04,166
Except one person, an ISIS member who was placed
here for just one hour, that is all

33
00:03:04,916 --> 00:03:08,708
Later I learned that ISIS had executed him
because his charge was fleeing from battle

34
00:03:08,750 --> 00:03:13,208
Or being a deserter, as they say,
or a runaway as they call it in military terms

35
00:03:14,166 --> 00:03:20,166
He was the only person who was placed here with me,
and the second person I saw was during interrogation, that is all

36
00:03:20,291 --> 00:03:22,583
Those are the only people I saw
during my imprisonment

37
00:03:23,333 --> 00:03:28,666
Until the last day, when I saw all the prisoners,
everyone, but I saw them in the tunnel
